# Normalize line endings across platforms.
#
# Why: Windows `core.autocrlf=true` was silently turning committed LF
# files into CRLF on checkout, which broke byte-exact snapshot tests
# (tests/fixtures/reports/sample-report.expected.md) and caused phantom
# "modified" status on .claude/** on every new worktree. Pinning line
# endings at the repo level removes both failure modes at once.
#
# `text=auto` lets git detect text vs binary; `eol=lf` forces LF in the
# working tree regardless of core.autocrlf. Real binary files are
# auto-detected and left alone.

* text=auto eol=lf
